Class DataManager

java.lang.Object
webfx.devs.DataManager
public class DataManager extends Object
A utility class for working with Data Objects.

This class is responsible for validating and transforming JSON input into usable Java structures, particularly the custom Data object. It is especially useful in cases where there is a need to bind frontend form data to backend Java objects.

It utilizes com.google.gson's JsonParser to efficiently serialize data, and uses Data objects for efficient retrieval and error handling.

    • jsonToData

      public static Data jsonToData(com.google.gson.JsonObject json)
      Converts a JsonObject to a Data object. Each key-value pair in the JsonObject is added to the map.

      Nested objects will be stored as instances of Data.

      Lists will be stored as instances of ArrayList

      Parameters:
      json - the JsonObject to be converted
      Returns:
      a HashMap containing the JSON key-value pairs, or null if an exception occurs

    • validateData

      public static Data validateData(Class<?> clazz, Data data)
      Asseses a Data object against a Class and determines if the fields of the object can match the types of the Class, for that attribute. For each attribute, we look for the corresponding key, meaning that if there is a Data key that does not map to an attribute's name, it does not become part of the returned Data object

      Meant to validate data, ensuring that it's values can fit to a class's types and handle situations where it cannot.

      The keys of json data must be identical to the names class's attributes. Using any null parameter returns null

      Parameters:
      clazz - The class that we are comparing attributes to
      data - , The data we are anyalyzing
      Returns:
      A Data object if data is valid, null otherwise
